"content": "<style>\nh1.thlex-title { font-size: 1.3em; margin: 0 0 0.4em; }\n.thlex-key { color: #888; font-size: 0.85em; font-weight: normal; margin-right: 0.4em; }\nnav.thlex-index { margin: 0.5em 0 0.75em; }\nnav.thlex-index ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2em; }\nnav.thlex-index li { margin: 0.15em 0; font-size: 0.95em; }\n.thlex-section { margin: 0.6em 0; }\nh2.thlex-heading { font-size: 1em; margin: 0.5em 0 0.2em; }\nh3.thlex-subheading { font-size: 0.95em; font-weight: normal; font-style: italic; margin: 0.2em 0; }\n.thlex-language-sets { margin: 0.3em 0 0.3em 1em; }\n.thlex-language-set { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 0.75em; border-left: 3px solid #e0e0e0; }\n.thlex-language { font-size: 0.8em; color: #888; margin-right: 0.4em; }\n.thlex-lemma { font-weight: bold; font-family: serif; }\n.thlex-translit { color: #555; font-style: italic; font-size: 0.9em; margin-left: 0.3em; }\n.thlex-refs { font-size: 0.85em; color: #444; margin-top: 0.15em; }\n.thlex-paragraphs p { margin: 0.35em 0; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.5; }\n.thlex-image { margin: 0.5em 0; display: block; }\n.thlex-image img { max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; }\nfigcaption.thlex-caption { font-size: 0.85em; color: #555; font-style: italic; margin-top: 0.2em; }\n.thlex-abbr { border-bottom: 1px dotted #888; cursor: help; }\n.thlex-xref { color: #1a5fb4; }\nspan[data-bnType=\"bibleReference\"] { color: #1a5fb4; }\ntable.thlex-table { border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.9em; margin: 0.5em 0; }\ntable.thlex-table td { padding: 0.2em 0.6em; vertical-align: top; border: 1px solid #ddd; }\ntable.thlex-table tr:first-child td { font-weight: bold; background: #f5f5f5; }\nul.thlex-index-list { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.6; }\nul.thlex-index-list ul { margin: 0.1em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; }\n.thlex-index-key { font-weight: bold; font-style: italic; }\n</style><h1 class=\"thlex-title\" id=\"REALIA:1.5.3.14\"><span class=\"thlex-key\">1.5.3.14</span> Dye</h1><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">References:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-sets\">\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">אדם</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(m’adam)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod25:5\">EXO 25:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod26:14\">EXO 26:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod35:7\">EXO 35:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod35:23\">EXO 35:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod36:19\">EXO 36:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod39:34\">EXO 39:34</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">צֶבַע</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(tseva‘)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg5:30\">JDG 5:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg5:30\">JDG 5:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg5:30\">JDG 5:30</a></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">Description and usage:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>Dye was a substance used to color materials, especially textiles. Dyes came from minerals, plants, insects (for example, all those based on the Hebrew root <em>tla‘</em> were from a small worm), and sea animals (in particular, certain mollusks).</p>\n<hr/>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">Translation:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>Translators and commentators differ concerning the exact meaning of the Hebrew word <em>m’adam</em>. Most understand it to mean that the rams’ skins or sheep­skins (which it always modifies) have been “dyed red” (<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Good News Translation (1992)\">GNT</abbr>, <abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"New International Version (1984)\">NIV</abbr>, <abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"New Jerusalem Bible (1985)\">NJB</abbr>) or “colored red” (<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"French Common Language Version (Bible en français courant)\">FRCL</abbr>, PV). However, <abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Revised Standard Version (1952)\">RSV</abbr>, <abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Contemporary English Version\">CEV</abbr>, and <abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Revised English Bible (1989)\">REB</abbr> say “tanned” (see <a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">1.13 Leather&lt;REALIA:1.13&gt;</a>).</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
